aa(lp26
VSo let me tell you a little bit
p27
aVabout what rating agencies really do.
p28
aVAs you would read a car magazine
p29
aVbefore purchasing a new car
p30
aVor taking a look at a product review
p31
aVbefore deciding which kind of tablet or phone to get,
p32
aVinvestors are reading ratings
p33
aVbefore they decide in which kind of product
p34
aVthey are investing their money.
p35
aVA rating can range from a so-called AAA,
p36
aVwhich means it's a top-performing product,
p37
aVand it can go down to the level
p38
aVof the so-called BBB-,
p39
aVwhich means it's a fairly risky investment.
p40
aVRating agencies are rating companies.
p41
aVThey are rating banks.
p42
aVThey are rating even financial products
p43
aVlike the infamous mortgage-backed securities.
p44
aVBut they can also rate countries,
p45
aVand these ratings are called sovereign ratings,
