aa(lp49
VAnd I can tell, as you're listening to me right now,
p50
aVyou're thinking,
p51
aVso why should I really care about this, right?
p52
aVBe honest.
p53
aVWell, ratings affect you.
p54
aVThey affect all of us.
p55
aVIf a rating agency rates a country,
p56
aVit basically assesses and evaluates
p57
aVa country's debt
p58
aVand the ability and willingness of a country
p59
aVto repay its debt.
p60
aVSo if a country gets downgraded by a rating agency,
p61
aVthe country has to pay more
p62
aVin order to borrow money
p63
aVon the international markets.
p64
aVSo it affects you as a citizen and as a taxpayer,
p65
aVbecause you and your fellow countrymen
p66
aVhave to pony up more in order to borrow.
p67
aVBut what if a country can't afford to pay more
p68
aVbecause it's maybe too expensive?
p69
aVWell, then the country has less available
p70
aVfor other services, like roads, schools, healthcare.
p71
aVAnd this is the reason why you should care,
p72
aVbecause sovereign ratings affect everyone.
p73
aVAnd that is the reason why I believe
p74
aVthey should be defined as public goods.
p75
aVThey should be transparent, accessible,
p76
aVand available to everyone at no cost.
