VBut here's the situation:
p79
aVthe rating agency market is dominated
p80
aVby three players and three players only \u2014
p81
aVStandard & Poor's, Moody's, and Fitch \u2014
p82
aVand we know whenever there is a market concentration,
p83
aVthere is really no competition.
p84
aVThere is no incentive to improve
p85
aVthe quality of your product.
p86
aVAnd let's face it, the credit rating  agencies have contributed,
p87
aVputting the global economy on the brink,
p88
aVand yet they have to change the way they operate.
