aa(lp148
VThe second big difference that INCRA would make is
p149
aVthat would it base its sovereign risk assessment
p150
aVon a broader set of indicators.
p151
aVThink about it that way.
p152
aVIf we conduct a sovereign rating,
p153
aVwe basically take a look at
p154
aVthe economic soil of a country,
p155
aVits macroeconomic fundamentals.
p156
aVBut we also have to ask the question,
p157
aVwho is cultivating the economic soil
p158
aVof a country, right?
p159
aVWell, a country has many gardeners,
p160
aVand one of them is the government,
p161
aVso we have to ask the question,
p162
aVhow is a country governed?
p163
aVHow is it managed?
p164
aVAnd this is the reason why we have developed
p165
aVwhat we call forward-looking indicators.
p166
aVThese are indicators that give you
p167
aVa much better read about
p168
aVthe socioeconomic development of a country.
p169
aVI hope you would agree it's important for you to know
p170
aVif your government is willing to invest  in renewable energy and education.
